Spec.title: Level 90 if you still didn't get Axe

PathOfBuilding.Notes:
^xFFFF77My league starter for 3.26, build that i already played in 3.25, but now it got some nice buffs.^7
^x70FF70So only thing that was changed is:^7 - ^xAF6025^7^xE05030Replica Wings of Entropy^7^7^7 received buff, more attack speed with main hand and way more flat crit chance with offhand. - On old setup with Ashes of the Stars offhand crit was already capped with old values, so build would only get around 10% more dps from more main hand attack speed. - But, now that axe can get up to 20% flat crit chance on offhand, ^xE05030Marylene's Fallacy^7 can be used and you still will be at 100% crit on offhand. - With buffed axe Marylene's Fallacy is actually slightly better than Ashes of the Stars, aside of being much cheaper and much more accessible!
!Old low budget setup had around ^xE050303.5mil dps^7, new low budget setup has over ^xE050305mil dps^7!
^x70FF70Tree (IMPORTANT):^7 - Trees are different before and after you get Replica Wings of Entropy. - Because Replica Wings of Entropy has unique modifier that make it count as both Two Handed and Dual Wield, so passives for both of those work with this weapon. ^xE05030^7^xE05030- Don't take any Two Handed passives! Change tree once you obtained the axe!^7 - ^xE05030Ascendancy: ^71. Explode on kill. 2-3. Block. 4. War of Attrition. ^7 ^xE05030^7^x70FF70Build is extremely simple, easy to level.^7^7^7 - You get ^xE05030Double Strike^7 from very beginning. - You use ^xE05030Splitting Steel^7 with ^xE05030Chance to Bleed^7 until you reach Tribal Fury with mastery for +1 target. - And from that moment you just use Double Strike. - Then just follow skills/supports in Skills menu. *Some of skills/support will be rewarded from quests, rest just buy from vendors in act 1-4.
^x70FF70Gear during campaign:^7 - 1H Axes. *You can also use 1H Axe with 1H sword and take Dual Wield mastery for 60% increased damage. Early its good. - Cap resists. ^x7070FF^xE05030- Change Rage Mastery to +7 Rage once you get Belt of the Deceiver, while you can skip it and keep using Intimidation Rage Mastery.^7^7
^x70FF70Gear after campaign:^7 - Two rare axes with highest phys dps you can find, then ^xE05030Replica Wings of Entropy^7 as soon as possible! - Rare gear: Life, Resists, some Str/Dex. - Pure Str armor. - ^xE05030Belt of Deceiver^7 is good early option. - ^xE05030Marylene's Fallacy^7 AFTER YOU GET THE AXE! - ^xE05030IMPORTANT: ^7Jewel with Mana Leech!
^x70FF70How to get Replica Wings of Entropy:^7 ^xE050301. ^7Buy, early might be expensive, day 2-3 will probably be dirt cheap. ^xE050302.^7 Or farm it yourself: - Take Heist stuff on Atlas Passive Tree, run Heist Contracts, then Blueprints. - This axe is fairly common there, but rng is rng, you might get it on first blueprint, or you might not. - Before running heist, prepare a bit, cap resists, get decent gear, since dying in heist cause you to lose all loot if you died after alarm was triggered. - Aside of that, you might get some expensive stuff which would allow you to sell it and just buy axe, unless youre doing ssf.
